> been informed by the mailing list that the original engine was fuel
> injected. Regardless it ran fine, started fine, took off fine and
//
> by hand. He told me the motor had seized. So I had the motor
> replaced. Just the motor. Now when I drive my van. I can't step on the
> gas and go. It has to warm up for a bit and even then the gas has to be
> pressed on with the touch of a feather. If you press on the gas too fast
> it will cut off, if warmed up then it stalls then ju
>  mps up to speed and still might cut off. when i do actually get it
